The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                The beheaded body of a 24-year-old youth, Hari Das, was found beside the railway tracks at Agarpara station on Wednesday morning. The head was traced half a kilometre away, close to Sodepur. GRP personnel said the head might have been severed in a train accident and carried away by a stray. Haris father Uttam Das, a trader of electrical goods in the area, said his son was undergoing psychiatric treatment.    A 32-year-old DYFI activist, Bijoy Shau, died after being shot from a close range in Titagarh in North 24-Parganas on Wednesday. Police said Shau was attacked by a group of criminals, who also lobbed crude bombs at him. He succumbed to his injuries at RG Kar hospital.     Akshay Shaw, 50, died after being hit by a private bus on route 1 while riding a bicycle on Central Garden Reach Road on Wednesday. He was admitted to SSKM Hospital in a critical condition but succumbed to his injuries. The bus driver fled without the vehicle, which was impounded.    One person was killed and two were seriously injured after a taxi and a minidor van collided while speeding near the Central Avenue-BB Ganguly Street crossing early on Wednesday. Police said the van driver, Pankaj Tewari, 26, was declared dead at Medical College and Hospital. His help and the taxi driver were admitted for treatment.     Five pairs of local trains in the Sealdah (South)-Diamond Harbour section will temporarily stop at Bahirpuya Halt station between March 19 and 22 on the occasion of Harinam Maha Yagna.    A delegation of the American Chamber of Commerce in India (Amcham) met the chief minister on Tuesday. This was inadvertently mentioned as the US-India Business Council in Metro on Wednesday. The Council had cancelled a trip to Calcutta during the Singur controversy in September 2008. The error is regretted.          Singer Ramkumar Chattopadhyay, 90, died at Belle Vue Clinic on Wednesday afternoon. According to the hospital authorities, the veteran exponent of toppa was admitted to the ICCU on March 9 with respiratory distress   because of a chest   infection. His mortal remains will be kept in the hospital mortuary overnight and taken to Rabindra Sadan and All India Radio on Thursday morning before reaching the Nimtala crematorium. He is survived by son   Srikumar Chattopadhyay, also a singer.                                                                                                                                                                
